704110f-a.title: Brooklyn: Emmons Avenue - Ocean Avenue
704110f-a.text:
Emmons Avenue, east from near Ocean Avenue, showing
the W. P. A. conducting highway operations tn conection
with the nity's belt parkway system. View 3 shows the
orth side of the avenue, viewing westward, the building
in Spanish architecture being Lundy's Restaurant.

706107f-a.title: Brooklyn: Ocean Avenue - Emmons Avenue
706107f-a.text:
Ocean Ave., west side, north from Emmons Ave. At the left, is the
new Lundy Bros., eating Palace; in the extreme bacllground, may be seen the
steeple of St. Mark's R.C. Church.
August 1, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
